import numpy as np
import random

def score(item, bins):
    max_capacity = np.max(bins)
    remaining_capacities = bins - item
    partially_used_bins = np.where(np.logical_and(bins >= item, bins < max_capacity))[0]
    num_partially_used_bins = len(partially_used_bins)
    random_numbers = np.random.rand(len(bins))
    scores = (bins - item) * 0.5 / ((bins / item) - np.floor(bins / item)) * (1.0 + np.square(np.exp(-(remaining_capacities / item)))) / (1.0 + np.sqrt(num_partially_used_bins)) * random_numbers
    return scores
